## Defensive Cyber Security Aka Blue Teaming(Blue Team)

##Roles Key Roles
- ⛨ SOC(Security Operations Centre ) Analyst -They monitor the organisations systems/networks and hardware in real time to spot, 
     suspiscious and expected threats or normal operations/ behaviours.

- 🤺 Incident Responder -These persons will be the first to respond to the incident. If the activity is confirmed to be a threats the IR(Incident Responder) 
      has to start containing, monitoring and prevent in real time(while threat is happening) the threat actors(Black Hats) and their method of attack.
      IR(Incident Responder) will also, gather information on what,when,where and how the bad actors(Black hats/Threat Actors) breached the system/network
      with the methods, targerts(who they attacked and what they attacked)they had used, gathering this information to further help protect the organisation.

- 🪪 Security Engineer -The Security Engineers typically help to develop and maintain security messuares and tools to further prevent and lowr the risk of,
      future attacks. They check the vectors(paths) threat actors(black hats/hackers) would and will most likely target. Security Engineers can do this manually or
      automisation.

- 🫆 Digital Forensics - These persons. will investigate what happend, by gather, preserving and analysing information, from the systems/networks that had been breached 
     and find any trace of the attack and attackers methods. DF's will always monitor the organisations systems/networks to see, 
     what is going on in the organisations networks and systems to see what is normal behaviour from users and employees and to see what is suspicious behaviour.
     DF's are always investigating and digging into and solving the puzzle as to speak, of the attack.
